The paper presents a novel approach for identifying rock type at the drilling bit using machine learning techniques for Measurements While Drilling (MWD) data. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of physical modeling of drilling mechanics, which suggests that it may also belong to the Scientific Computing and Computational Physics (cs.SI) sub-category. The paper also deals with classification, which is a common topic in the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the development of a model for a specific application, which suggests that it may also belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
